data.name: Bellsprout
data.flavorText: Even though its body is extremely skinny, it is blindingly fast when catching its prey.

data.name: Weepinbell
data.flavorText: The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.

data.name: Victreebel
data.flavorText: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

data.name: Petilil
data.flavorText: Although the leaves on its head are bitter enough to cause dizziness, they provide relief from weariness—even more so when boiled.

data.name: Lilligant
data.flavorText: No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.

data.name: Phantump
data.flavorText: These Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died in the forest. Their cries sound like eerie screams.

data.name: Trevenant
data.flavorText: This Pokémon is said to devour anyone daring to ravage the forest. To the creatures dwelling in the forest, it offers great kindness.

data.name: Wimpod
data.flavorText: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.

data.name: Golisopod
data.flavorText: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.

data.name: Victini
data.flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

data.name: Litwick
data.flavorText: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.

data.name: Lampent
data.flavorText: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.

data.name: Chandelure
data.flavorText: Being consumed in Chandelure's flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.

data.name: Oricorio
data.flavorText: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

data.name: Salandit
data.flavorText: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

data.name: Salazzle
data.flavorText: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.

data.name: Turtonator
data.flavorText: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

data.name: Alolan Sandshrew
data.flavorText: It lives on snowy mountains. Its steel shell is very hard—so much so, it can't roll its body up into a ball.

data.name: Alolan Sandshrew
data.flavorText: It lives on snowy mountains. Its steel shell is very hard—so much so, it can't roll its body up into a ball.

data.name: Alolan Sandslash
data.flavorText: Fleeing a volcanic eruption, it settled on a snowy mountain. As it races through the snowfields, it sends up a spray of snow.

data.name: Alolan Vulpix
data.flavorText: It exhales air colder than -58 degrees Fahrenheit. Elderly people in Alola call this Pokémon by an older name—Keokeo.

data.name: Alolan Vulpix
data.flavorText: It exhales air colder than -58 degrees Fahrenheit. Elderly people in Alola call this Pokémon by an older name—Keokeo.

data.name: Tentacool
data.flavorText: They can be found lying dehydrated on beaches, but they are often still alive. When soaked in water, they will revive.

data.name: Tentacruel
data.flavorText: Normally, it has 80 poisonous tentacles. The longer one has been alive, the fewer tentacles it will have.

data.name: Politoed
data.flavorText: They gather on moonlit nights to form a large chorus. Their cries sound angry and not at all pleasant, but they are certainly distinctive.

data.name: Delibird
data.flavorText: Although it naturally prefers colder locales, Delibird in Alola seem able to withstand the heat to a certain extent.

data.name: Carvanha
data.flavorText: Each school has its own territory. Any intruders are mercilessly attacked with fangs bared.

data.name: Sharpedo
data.flavorText: It pursues its prey at speeds of 75 mph and finishes them off with fangs that can crush iron. It is known as the bully of the sea.

data.name: Wailmer
data.flavorText: It loves to startle people. It fills itself up with seawater and plays by bouncing around like a ball.

data.name: Wailord
data.flavorText: Wailord pursue their prey in pods. With their large mouths, they can swallow entire schools of Wishiwashi whole.

data.name: Snorunt
data.flavorText: Their numbers seem to have rapidly increased in Alola. Custom has it that houses where Snorunt live will be prosperous for generations to come.

data.name: Glalie
data.flavorText: Legend says a boulder on an icy mountain absorbed the distress and regrets of a stranded mountaineer, giving rise to Glalie.

data.name: Vanillite
data.flavorText: Born of an icicle, this Pokémon uses its frosty breath to make ice crystals, causing snow to fall.

data.name: Vanillish
data.flavorText: Hot days cause its body to melt. It can be restored by refreezing it, but the process leaves its body slightly warped.

data.name: Vanilluxe
data.flavorText: Each of its two heads has a brain, and when they are in agreement, it attacks its enemies by exhaling a violent blizzard.

data.name: Alomomola
data.flavorText: It uses its special mucus to close the wounds of injured Pokémon. The reason for this behavior remains unknown.

data.name: Wishiwashi
data.flavorText: When it's in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.

data.name: Mareanie
data.flavorText: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

data.name: Alolan Geodude
data.flavorText: Its body is a magnetic stone. Iron sand attaches firmly to the portions of its body that are particularly magnetic.

data.name: Alolan Graveler
data.flavorText: Its preferred food is dravite. After it has eaten this mineral, crystals form inside the Pokémon, rising to the surface of part of its body.

data.name: Alolan Golem
data.flavorText: It fires rocks charged with electricity. Even if the rock isn't fired that accurately, just grazing an opponent will cause numbness and fainting.

data.name: Helioptile
data.flavorText: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

data.name: Heliolisk
data.flavorText: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

data.name: Oricorio
data.flavorText: This Oricorio has sipped bright yellow nectar. Its bright, cheerful dance melts the hearts of its enemies.

data.name: Slowpoke
data.flavorText: Its long tail often breaks off. It doesn't really feel any pain, though, and the tail grows back, so Slowpoke isn't particularly bothered.

data.name: Slowbro
data.flavorText: It spaces out while gazing at the sea. With Shellder's poison flowing through its body, it becomes even spacier.

data.name: Trubbish
data.flavorText: Unsanitary places are what they like best. They can be spotted in Alola, often with Grimer in hot pursuit.

data.name: Garbodor
data.flavorText: Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots from its right arm. If even a little of it gets on you, you'll experience the effects of the unidentified toxin.

data.name: Garbodor
data.flavorText: Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots from its right arm. If even a little of it gets on you, you'll experience the effects of the unidentified toxin.

data.name: Gothita
data.flavorText: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

data.name: Gothorita
data.flavorText: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.

data.name: Gothitelle
data.flavorText: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

data.name: Oricorio
data.flavorText: This Oricorio relaxes by swaying gently. This increases its psychic energy, which it then fires at its enemies.

data.name: Oricorio
data.flavorText: This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Its elegant, attractive dance will send the minds and hearts of its enemies to another world.

data.name: Mimikyu
data.flavorText: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by horror and died of the shock.

data.name: Dhelmise
data.flavorText: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.

data.name: Lunala
data.flavorText: It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog. When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world.

data.name: Machop
data.flavorText: It loves working out. As it gazes at its muscles, which continue to swell day by day, it becomes more and more dedicated to its training.

data.name: Machop
data.flavorText: It loves working out. As it gazes at its muscles, which continue to swell day by day, it becomes more and more dedicated to its training.

data.name: Machoke
data.flavorText: As a result of its continual workouts, it has developed tremendous power. It uses that power to help people with their work.

data.name: Machamp
data.flavorText: It unleashes megaton-level punches that send opponents flying clear over the horizon.

data.name: Sudowoodo
data.flavorText: To avoid attack, it mimics a tree. It will run off if splashed with water, which it hates.

data.name: Gligar
data.flavorText: It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

data.name: Gliscor
data.flavorText: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

data.name: Nosepass
data.flavorText: The magnet in Nosepass's nose provides an unerring compass, making it an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.

data.name: Barboach
data.flavorText: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey's location.

data.name: Whiscash
data.flavorText: A glutton that devours anything that moves, it quietly lurks at the bottom of swamps, lying in wait for prey.

data.name: Pancham
data.flavorText: It grows up imitating the behavior of Pangoro, which it looks up to as a leader.

data.name: Rockruff
data.flavorText: It's considered to be a good Pokémon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.

data.name: Mudbray
data.flavorText: The mud stuck to Mudbray's hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.

data.name: Mudsdale
data.flavorText: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.

data.name: Minior
data.flavorText: It eats dust in the atmosphere. The composition of the dust determines the color of its core.

data.name: Murkrow
data.flavorText: They awaken at dusk and take wing in the twilight, leading to the expression, "Get home before the Murkrow fly."

data.name: Honchkrow
data.flavorText: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than a hundred of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.

data.name: Sableye
data.flavorText: It's a fiend for gemstones, so it stalks Carbink. Unfortunately, Gabite almost always grabs them first.

data.name: Absol
data.flavorText: Long ago, superstitions were spread about it, saying it brought disaster. This fed a hatred of it, and it was driven deep into the mountains.

data.name: Pangoro
data.flavorText: It boasts superb physical strength. Those who wish to become Pangoro's Trainer have no choice but to converse with their fists.

data.name: Beldum
data.flavorText: Its cells are all magnets. It uses magnetism to communicate with others of its kind.

data.name: Metang
data.flavorText: When two Beldum link together, their psychic power is doubled. Their intelligence, however, remains unchanged.

data.name: Probopass
data.flavorText: It radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances become unusable.

data.name: Solgaleo
data.flavorText: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.

data.name: Clefairy
data.flavorText: Its adorable behavior and appearance make it popular with men and women, young and old. Its numbers are few, however.

data.name: Clefable
data.flavorText: They don't like to reveal themselves in front of people. They live quietly in packs deep in the mountains.

data.name: Cottonee
data.flavorText: When it finds others of its kind, they all stick together. When enough of them have collected, the mass resembles a cumulonimbus cloud.

data.name: Whimsicott
data.flavorText: It rides on the wind and slips into people's homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton-filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.

data.name: Comfey
data.flavorText: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.

data.name: Goomy
data.flavorText: The weakest of all Dragon-type Pokémon, it's unable to breathe if its skin dries out, so it sticks to shady places.

data.name: Sliggoo
data.flavorText: It has trouble drawing a line between friends and food. It will calmly try to melt and eat even those it gets along well with.

data.name: Goodra
data.flavorText: An amazingly friendly Pokémon, but if left to itself, loneliness overcomes it, and it oozes gooey tears.

data.name: Drampa
data.flavorText: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it will completely destroy its surroundings with its intense breath.

data.name: Jangmo-o
data.flavorText: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.

data.name: Hakamo-o
data.flavorText: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.

data.name: Chansey
data.flavorText: The eggs laid by Chansey are rich in nutrients and a favorite food of many Pokémon.

data.name: Blissey
data.flavorText: Even the most ferocious Pokémon become calm when they eat Blissey's egg, which is said to be filled with happiness.

data.name: Taillow
data.flavorText: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

data.name: Swellow
data.flavorText: If its two tail feathers are standing at attention, it is proof of good health. It soars elegantly in the sky.

data.name: Castform
data.flavorText: It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.

data.name: Rayquaza
data.flavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

data.name: Patrat
data.flavorText: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

data.name: Watchog
data.flavorText: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.

data.name: Fletchling
data.flavorText: This amiable Pokémon is easy to train. But when battle is joined, it shows its ferocious side.

data.name: Fletchinder
data.flavorText: From its beak, it fires embers at its prey. Once it has caught them, it grills them at high heat before feasting upon them.

data.name: Talonflame
data.flavorText: Its favorite foods are Wingull and Pikipek. It attacks with a powerful kick and grasps them firmly in its talons.

data.name: Stufful
data.flavorText: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

data.name: Bewear
data.flavorText: This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.

data.name: Komala
data.flavorText: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.
